HEADWORD: Efflower
<hw>Ef*flow"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>effleurer</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Leather Making)</fld> <def>To remove
the epidermis of (a skin) with a concave knife, blunt in its middle
part, -- as in making chamois leather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effluence</ent>⟦br⟧
